comments: Mobley (CLE) is imminently exiting the lane within three seconds.
Beverley (PHI) cleanly blocks Garland's (CLE) driving shot attempt.
Mobley (CLE) deflects the ball away from Melton (PHI) during the rebound.
Melton (PHI) reaches in and dislodges the ball from Wade (CLE).
Garland (CLE) slightly extends his leg after the release of his jump shot attempt and makes contact with Beverley (PHI), which is marginal and does not affect his ability to defend.
Embiid (PHI) legally takes two steps upon receiving the pass as a progressing player.
Allen (CLE) legally contests Embiid's (PHI) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Wade (CLE) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs during Maxey's (PHI) driving shot attempt.
Beverley (PHI) reaches in and pulls Allen's (CLE) right arm, affecting his ability to gain possession of the ball.
Wade (CLE) engages and disengages with Embiid (PHI) in the post as both players attempt to establish position.
As Embiid (PHI) is pivoting, he slightly extends his forearm into Mobley's (CLE) body, which does not dislodge him from his legally obtained position.
Allen (PHI) grazes Beverley's (PHI) arm, which does not affect his ability to control the rebound.
Strus (CLE) brushes Beverley's (PHI) arm as he attempts to dislodge the ball and the contact does not affect Beverley's ability to release the pass.
Beverley (PHI) leans into Garland (CLE) and initiates contact with his right shoulder, affecting his shot attempt.
Harris (PHI) establishes himself in a screening position and collapses his arms as he braces from the incoming contact from Thompson during the screen.
Thompson (CLE) legally contests Embiid's (PHI) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Melton (PHI) places his forearm on Garland's (CLE) body during his driving shot attempt and the contact is marginal.
Wade (CLE) moves alongside Maxey's (PHI) path during the drive and the contact as Maxey attempts to release his pass is marginal.
Wade (CLE) collapses his forearm and the body contact underneath the basket with Embiid (PHI) is marginal.
Harris (PHI) reaches in and initiates contact with Mobley's (CLE) arm, which affects his play at the basket.
Strus (CLE) reaches in and grazes Maxey's (PHI) body after the release of his jump shot attempt.
Mobley (CLE) controls the rebound and incidental arm contact occurs with Beverley (PHI) as he reaches for the ball.
Maxey (PHI) reaches in and makes slight contact to Porter's (CLE) body at the start of the drive, which does not affect his SQBR.
Embiid (PHI) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs during Porter's (CLE) driving shot attempt.
Embiid (PHI) establishes himself in a screening position and is firming up when he brushes Strus' (CLE) body during the pick, which does not affect his ability to defend.
Embiid (PHI) slightly extends his arm into Allen's (CLE) body during the drive, which does not dislodge him from his legally obtained position.
Allen (CLE) establishes himself in Beverley's (PHI) path and is firming up when he absorbs the incoming contact during the pick.
Beverley (PHI) moves alongside of Garland (CLE) and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Embiid (PHI) legally makes contact to the ball while the ball is rolling off of the rim and not using the rim as its lower base.
Batum (PHI) is last to make contact with the ball prior to it going out of bounds.
Embiid (PHI) extends his right leg into Garland's (CLE) path, initiating contact with Garland's right leg that affects his SQBR and causes him to trip.
Reed (PHI) collapses his arms as he absorbs the incoming contact from Wade (CLE) during the pick.
Maxey (PHI) slightly extends his arm and releases from Allen (CLE), which does not affect his ability to defend.
Maxey (PHI) gathers the ball on his right foot and takes two) steps before his jump shot attempt.
Maxey (PHI) does not overtly or abruptly extend his leg out as incidental contact occurs with Allen (CLE) during his legal contest of the jump shot attempt.
Wade (CLE) cleanly deflects the inbounds pass intended for Melton (PHI).
The ball makes contact to Wade's (CLE) arm prior to it going out of bounds.
